<br>
Isn't the point to have fun? You have the most fun when you're up against challenging situations. And you can take pride in doing it yourself - developing the tactics, gearing up your teammates, supporting each other, and generally having a good time.<br>
<br>
I really think the desire to join uber guilds is generally greed. What's the different between a Kael raid and a VT raid? It's all a matter of scale. They drop grear appropriate to your capability, and allow people to get better. You have to work together as a team and you get rewards. <br>
<br>
Participate, lead raids, support your friends and have fun. I think you'll find that to be way more entertaining than being a cog in a raiding guild.<br>
<br>
If you level to 60 in Velks and then tag on 150 AA points, just so you can join a raiding guild, I really think you're completely missing the point of the *GAME*.<br>
<br>
Rogok - 55 Ogre Warrior<br>
Saryrn<br>
Darkholme's Big Red Machine<br>
